#compdef node-pre-gyp
# =============================================================================
# node-pre-gyp — Mapbox's "node.js native add-on binary install tool"
#                 — a Node.js CLI for downloading + verifying +
#                 unpacking PREBUILT BINARIES for native Node.js
#                 modules.  Native modules (those with C/C++/Rust
#                 code) traditionally require compilation against
#                 the user's Node.js headers at install time via
#                 `node-gyp`, which:
#                   - Requires Python + a C++ toolchain on every
#                     user's machine
#                   - Takes 30s-5min per package install
#                   - Breaks when the user's compiler version
#                     mismatches the module's expectations
#                   - Fails on Windows without Visual Studio
#                 `node-pre-gyp` solves this by letting MODULE
#                 AUTHORS prebuild binaries for every popular
#                 OS+CPU+Node-version combination (~30 variants),
#                 upload them to S3 / GitHub Releases / CDN,
#                 and have `npm install` download the appropriate
#                 prebuilt binary instead of compiling.  The
#                 module's `package.json` declares a `binary`
#                 section pointing to the binary host + filename
#                 templates; node-pre-gyp inspects the user's
#                 platform, downloads the correct .tar.gz, and
#                 unpacks it into the module's build directory —
#                 zero compilation, zero toolchain dependency.
#                 USED BY: sqlite3, sharp (Image processing,
#                 pre-fork), grpc, mapnik, sass, fsevents, and
#                 dozens of other widely-deployed npm packages.
#                 Originally written by Mapbox engineering team
#                 (Dane Springmeyer + Konstantin Käfer) circa
#                 2014; the maintained fork now lives at
#                 @mapbox/node-pre-gyp on npm.
#
# Author:  Mapbox (Dane Springmeyer led; Konstantin Käfer
#          contributed) — initially built to ship Mapbox's heavy
#          native-binding stack (mapnik, sqlite, geos) without
#          forcing every Mapbox SDK user to install a complete
#          C++ toolchain.  Open-sourced under BSD-3-Clause.
# Source:  https://github.com/mapbox/node-pre-gyp
#          (now archived; maintained fork at
#           https://github.com/mapbox/node-pre-gyp under
#           @mapbox/node-pre-gyp on npm; the original
#           `node-pre-gyp` package is also published)
# CLI:     lib/node-pre-gyp.js exports a `Run` class that
#          parses argv via `nopt(configDefs, shorthands, argv)`;
#          the bin script `bin/node-pre-gyp` instantiates `Run`
#          and dispatches to command handlers in lib/<cmd>.js
#          (lib/install.js, lib/build.js, lib/clean.js, etc).
# Library: nopt
#          ("Node/npm option parser" — npm's argv parser written
#           by Isaac Z. Schlueter circa 2010 for the original npm
#           CLI.  nopt is built around TYPE COERCION: callers
#           declare a TYPES DICTIONARY mapping flag names to
#           type constructors (Boolean, String, Number, Date,
#           url.parse, path), and nopt parses argv into a JS
#           object whose values are type-coerced + validated.
#           A separate SHORTHANDS DICTIONARY maps short forms
#           ("-C" → "--directory") and value-binding aliases
#           ("--silent" → "--loglevel=silent").)
# License: BSD-3-Clause (node-pre-gyp); ISC (nopt)
# Status:  Active maintenance — node-pre-gyp is on long-term
#          maintenance mode under @mapbox; nopt itself is npm-
#          inc/nopt, still actively maintained by the npm/cli
#          team (last commit 2024).  Used as a direct dependency
#          by 3,000+ npm packages including major native-add-on
#          publishers.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY MILESTONE — TS-NODE CROSSES TO 48
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# With this completion the cross-language CLI library taxonomy documents
# the 48TH TypeScript-Node CLI library variant.  TypeScript-Node climbs
